- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper introduces a new synchronisation mechanism that enables non-deterministic behaviours and multiparty sessions. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new system for defining multiparty sessions. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention any machine learning techniques or applications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a less likely category as the paper does not focus on data structures or algorithms.
